File: After a tug-of-war over viewing rights, the games will not be broadcast on SABC platforms. JOHANNESBURG - The battle over the broadcasting of PSL matches between the SABC and the PSL has come to an end. Sports Minister Nathi Mthethwa and Communications Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams announced a resolution has been found. It comes after they met with the SABC board and Multichoice. READ: Still no PSL matches on SABC TV, radio The public broadcaster has been holding talks with the PSL for the past two weeks. The blackout has seen no PSL matches broadcast on either radio or television on SABC channels since the start of the season in early August. This was due to a payment disagreement. The ministers say full details of the agreement will be released on Friday.